You expect too much and are using the wrong tool. Perhaps if they renamed this board to "vomit" - you might remember what the board really is.

A place where anything goes. That's it. Postards who can't limit discussions to politics are just part of the landscape.

Now if you are arguing for places where idiots can be shut out - I agree. /pol really needs a process where interested parties could move their discussions into private retroshare or telegram groups. 

I'm certain some good cryptographer could figure this out. A means to protect invites. Perhaps even extend it to "cells"...where an individual could betray only two others at best.

posts.subject: Making the rounds this morning
Biden Road Trip
posts.body:
>>55ba8f5b-cd48-4db1-8aec-9191a6070942
BIDEN finally breaks down and visits a remote northern reservation.  With news crews following him around as they tour the place, the President asks the chief if there was anything they need.
"Well," says the chief, "We have three very important needs.  First, we have a medical clinic but no doctor to man it."

Biden whips out his cell phone, dials a number, talks to somebody for two minutes and then hangs up. "I've pulled some strings. Your doctor will arrive in a few days. Now what was the second problem?"

"We have no way to get clean water. The local mining operation has poisoned the water our people have been drinking for dozens of years.  We've been flying bottled water in, and it's terribly expensive."  Once again, Biden dials a number, yells into the cell phone for a few minutes, and then hangs up. "The mine has been shut down, and the owner is being billed for setting up a purification plant for your people. Now what was that third problem?"

The chief looks at him and says, "We have no cellphone reception up here!"

posts.subject: Interesting. Website is gone.
posts.body:
Following the events of January 6th, 2021, it became clear media and law enforcement were attempting to dox and interview the domain owner (me) regarding the site and user content. Unfortunately, the mod team had been struggling for some time to address a flood of racist and violent content that appeared to be coming primarily from a small group of extremists who were often brigading from other sites. This had led to warnings from Epik (domain registrar) and inquiries from the FBI.

Seems to have been moved to: https://patriots.win/

Have no idea who these people are, but always wondered if they'd be safe messing with the clearnet. It's too easy to silence people given the clearnet's structure.

In today's climate, I can't see how even a permanent "Handshake" based address would protect you.

Nope, right now onions, I2P, and Zeronet are your only real protection. Loki might qualify eventually...but not yet. Too many unknowns.

posts.subject: Two Virologists
posts.body:
Heavily compressed to fit within the constraints of email

Two virologists. Their occupation requires vaccinations far in excess of anything the US public would require. They are wary of these Covid vaccinations. "New technology - too little is known". They would be fine with a Covid vaccine produced with traditional methods.

My take? Too risky for young people. They might be better off riding the tiger. Older people have fewer options for survival - so might be a bet worth taking.

The real concern is reproduction. Both females and males may be vulnerable.

posts.subject: Time admits the coup was real
posts.body:
Even many of Trump's supporters never liked the guy. He wasn't a likeable player.

But when you cheat and take away our vote - you have sealed your fate. Time will prove this was a horrendous mistake on your part.

Your single path for atonement? Give us a voting system as secure as Mexico's. Otherwise it starts now.

>>d67cb2f6-6358-48ba-be9a-f8646c8ce970
You will never be able to compete with their resources. Your resource level hangs by a thread. Therefore making your existing ammo count is more important.

Worry more that civilians don't have the technology to crack those ceramic vests when storm troopers come. At least not easily, and not in a portable package. Only the military has the XM1186. And there's no question it will be used on Americans should they become armored. Those who aren't droned.

Politicians, corporations, and "activists" are softer targets. You still may have no recourse but to use your dead man's switch when storm troopers come and escape becomes impossible. Just reality.  They will ALWAYS be more powerful than you. 

NEVER make enemies you can avoid. This nonsense about shutting down cities via the power grid is guaranteed to generate pushback from normies. Should be reserved only for cities you intend to reduce into cannibalism.

We need a reproducible conventional cartridge handload for cracking ceramic armor. May not be possible.
